02:40.176 --> 02:42.595
What the hell is keeping Diane?

02:42.595 --> 02:44.597
I'm gonna be late for school.

02:44.597 --> 02:45.598
School, Carla?

02:45.598 --> 02:47.600
Well, I must say I'm
delightfully astonished.

02:47.600 --> 02:49.602
You know, I've always
held that adult education

02:50.103 --> 02:52.105
is one of the finest gifts
that one can give oneself.

02:52.105 --> 02:54.107
Kudos on joining the
ever-burgeoning ranks

02:54.107 --> 02:55.608
of enlightened, wondering minds

02:55.608 --> 02:57.110
seeking betterment through knowledge.

02:57.110 --> 02:59.612
It's traffic school, you nimrod.

03:01.998 --> 03:02.782
You got pinched, huh, Carla?

03:02.782 --> 03:04.284
Yeah, speeding.

03:04.284 --> 03:05.285
But it wasn't my fault.

03:05.785 --> 03:07.787
There was a leaf stuck on my windshield,

03:07.787 --> 03:10.790
and I had to gun her
up to 80 to blow it off.

03:12.292 --> 03:14.177
What, and the cop didn't believe you?

03:14.177 --> 03:15.929
No. Couldn't be bribed, either.

03:15.929 --> 03:19.432
Carla, what, you offered
a policeman money?

03:19.432 --> 03:21.935
Money? With a body like this? Huh.

03:24.437 --> 03:25.939
Hello, everyone.

03:25.939 --> 03:27.440
We're back.

03:27.440 --> 03:28.942
Sammy, where you been, man?

03:28.942 --> 03:30.860
Picking china patterns.

03:32.729 --> 03:37.483
This may have been the
stupidest morning of my life.

03:37.483 --> 03:38.985
Oh, Sam, don't forget.

03:38.985 --> 03:41.487
Tomorrow we register for flatware.

03:41.487 --> 03:43.489
The second stupidest.

03:43.489 --> 03:44.874
Well, did you select something nice?

03:44.874 --> 03:47.877
We've committed to
Royal Doulton's Carlisle

03:47.877 --> 03:49.629
for the fine china,

03:49.629 --> 03:51.965
but Sam still hasn't made up his mind

03:51.965 --> 03:53.967
about the everyday ware.

03:53.967 --> 03:55.468
Yes, I have.

03:55.468 --> 03:58.471
I, I like the dishes with
the different colored flowers.

03:58.471 --> 03:59.973
Oh, ish!

03:59.973 --> 04:01.474
Come on, I love those.

04:01.474 --> 04:03.977
They're just like I
had when I was a kid.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.428
They're real pretty,

04:05.428 --> 04:07.931
and-and if you don't like
the food on your plate,

04:07.931 --> 04:09.432
you can hide it in the pattern.

04:11.935 --> 04:13.436
Okay, fine.

04:13.436 --> 04:15.939
Well, uh, why don't you think about it,

04:15.939 --> 04:16.940
and if you still insist

04:17.440 --> 04:21.444
that they're not the
most garish, bourgeois,

04:21.444 --> 04:22.946
stomach-turningly ugly
pattern in the book,

04:22.946 --> 04:23.947
then that's what we'll get.

04:25.698 --> 04:28.034
She's making me nuts

04:28.034 --> 04:29.285
with this wedding stuff.

04:29.285 --> 04:30.586
So, ditch her.

04:30.586 --> 04:33.589
You know, if I had my way,

04:33.589 --> 04:35.591
I would find the nearest
justice of the peace

04:36.092 --> 04:37.093
and, and tie the knot.

04:37.093 --> 04:38.962
You know, that's not such a bad idea.

04:38.962 --> 04:40.296
Right. Or you could ditch her.

04:40.296 --> 04:43.683
Don't you have traffic
school, or something?

04:43.683 --> 04:45.468
Nuts! Now I'm gonna be late!

04:45.468 --> 04:49.472
Well, I guess I can make
it if I run all the yellows.

04:51.474 --> 04:53.476
Sam... Yo.

04:53.476 --> 04:56.479
I've got Penelope from the
bridal registry on the line,

04:56.479 --> 04:57.480
and we're going back

04:57.480 --> 04:58.982
over the linen choices.

04:59.482 --> 05:01.484
Now, for the fingertip towels

05:01.484 --> 05:03.987
in the guest bath, do
we want monogrammed,

05:03.987 --> 05:05.488
or is that too ootsie?

05:05.488 --> 05:07.874
The second thing you said.

05:09.375 --> 05:11.878
I agree.

05:11.878 --> 05:16.382
Of course... a simple
initial can be elegant.

05:16.382 --> 05:18.384
Oh, I think you'd better
look at the picture.

05:18.384 --> 05:19.886
I need a man's opinion.

05:19.886 --> 05:22.889
Frasier, help Diane, will you please?

05:25.391 --> 05:27.894
Sam, these will be our fingertip towels

05:27.894 --> 05:29.896
for the rest of our lives.

05:36.936 --> 05:39.939
We'd better get married
quick, or I'm gonna kill her.

05:41.941 --> 05:44.444
All right, all right, that's it.

05:44.444 --> 05:46.329
Bachelor party here tonight.

05:46.329 --> 05:47.747
What are you talking about?

05:47.747 --> 05:48.748
Well, didn't you hear the man?

05:48.748 --> 05:50.249
Uh, they might be eloping.

05:50.249 --> 05:52.118
And I'm not gonna be, uh, done out

05:52.118 --> 05:52.919
of my right as best man

05:53.419 --> 05:55.421
to, uh, throw him the best
wingding of the century.

05:55.922 --> 05:57.924
All right now, so
what're we gonna have...?

05:57.924 --> 05:59.425
Just a second here, Cliff.

05:59.425 --> 06:02.295
Uh, Sam asked you to be his best man?

06:02.295 --> 06:03.179
Well, not in so many words,

06:03.179 --> 06:04.680
but, uh, you know, who's closest?

06:04.680 --> 06:06.099
So, uh... (everybody talking)

06:06.099 --> 06:08.017
Hold on now, I don't know.

06:08.017 --> 06:10.520
I may not have known Sam
as long as some of you guys,

06:10.520 --> 06:12.522
but we're pretty darned close.

06:12.522 --> 06:15.024
I think I'm kind of like
the brother he never had.

06:15.024 --> 06:17.026
Wait, Woody, Sam has a brother.

06:17.026 --> 06:20.530
Guess we're not as close as I thought.

06:20.530 --> 06:22.532
Well, look, I think we better throw

06:22.532 --> 06:24.033
the greatest bachelor party

06:24.033 --> 06:26.402
for the greatest
bachelor who ever lived.

06:26.402 --> 06:27.870
Tell you what.

06:27.870 --> 06:29.872
I'll pick up some deli
platters and some champagne,

06:29.872 --> 06:30.873
and you guys can just reimburse me,

06:30.873 --> 06:32.375
you know, at your leisure, all right?

06:32.375 --> 06:34.377
CLIFF: Why didn't you
say so in the first place?

06:34.377 --> 06:36.379
Okay, we got the food and
the drink taken care of.

06:36.379 --> 06:37.880
Now we need a little
bit of entertainment.

06:37.880 --> 06:39.382
Who's gonna...?

06:39.382 --> 06:41.384
Well, I-I think
tradition calls for, uh,

06:41.384 --> 06:42.385
what about a stag film, huh?

06:42.385 --> 06:44.253
Yeah, yeah. Yeah, I think there's

06:44.253 --> 06:46.506
a place on my route
that might sell them.

06:46.506 --> 06:49.008
Uh, the, uh, Hot and
Nasty Video Boutique.

06:50.009 --> 06:53.012
Yeah, I think there might be
one or two laying around there.

06:53.012 --> 06:55.515
Okay, we got the food,
drink, entertainment.

06:55.515 --> 06:56.516
Now all we need is a, uh,

06:56.516 --> 06:58.434
a girl jumping out of the cake.

06:58.434 --> 06:59.435
(general agreement)

06:59.435 --> 07:01.320
Oh, yeah, I've seen them do that

07:01.320 --> 07:02.822
in the movies all the time.

07:02.822 --> 07:05.191
That seems like a waste
of good cake to me.

07:07.493 --> 07:08.744
You see, Woody, the cake

07:08.744 --> 07:09.529
is really immaterial.

07:09.529 --> 07:11.030
It's the girl who's the actual dessert.

07:11.030 --> 07:12.532
Right.

07:12.532 --> 07:14.534
Well, then I think it
should be Miss Chambers.

07:14.534 --> 07:15.785
FRASIER: Ooh. Aw, come on.

07:15.785 --> 07:17.620
Ee-i-ee-i-oh!

07:17.620 --> 07:21.124
Hey, listen, tractor-boy...

07:21.124 --> 07:23.126
you know,

07:23.126 --> 07:25.628
no guy wants his fiancée
jumping out of a cake.

07:25.628 --> 07:29.132
It's, I mean, it's like
taking your mother to the prom.

07:29.132 --> 07:31.134
(chuckling)

07:31.134 --> 07:33.136
Or so I'm told.

07:38.641 --> 07:39.642
PAUL: Okay, okay, okay,

07:40.143 --> 07:42.145
so where can we get Sammy someone hot?

07:42.645 --> 07:44.147
Dare we look in his book?

07:44.147 --> 07:46.649
Nah, Sammy's had all those girls.

07:47.150 --> 07:49.152
Oh, Sam, stop being
such a grumble-bunny.

07:49.152 --> 07:51.654
Just grit your teeth and
pick out a dust ruffle.

07:54.657 --> 07:55.658
Guys, I still say

07:55.658 --> 07:57.660
we're missing a bet
right under our noses.

07:57.660 --> 07:59.162
Look, pal, trust me...

07:59.162 --> 08:00.663
Oh, it's... that's okay.

08:00.663 --> 08:02.665
Listen, I... it wouldn't hurt to ask.

08:02.665 --> 08:04.167
CLIFF: No, no, no, no, don't, don't...

08:04.167 --> 08:05.668
Excuse me, Miss Chambers?

08:05.668 --> 08:07.170
Yes, Woody? Uh...

08:07.670 --> 08:10.173
Uh, would you like to jump out
of Sam's bachelor party cake?

08:10.173 --> 08:17.647
Woody, I abhor such
juvenile, sexist male rituals.

08:17.647 --> 08:19.849
Yeah, but would you do it?

08:21.150 --> 08:22.018
Just checking.

08:22.018 --> 08:23.486
All right, guys, you're right.

08:23.486 --> 08:24.987
We're going to have to find

08:24.987 --> 08:27.356
some other beautiful
girl to be Sam's dessert.

08:27.356 --> 08:30.109
Wait a minute.

08:30.109 --> 08:34.113
(laughing)

08:34.113 --> 08:35.615
I, I just realized

08:35.615 --> 08:38.618
why you want me,
the bride-to-be,

08:38.618 --> 08:41.120
to jump from the cake.

08:41.120 --> 08:43.121
It's a wonderful irony.

08:43.121 --> 08:44.373
(laughs)

08:44.373 --> 08:45.541
Oh...

08:45.541 --> 08:47.009
Of course I'll do it.

08:47.009 --> 08:48.010
Of course.

08:48.010 --> 08:49.011
Oh, great.

08:49.011 --> 08:50.963
Imagine me, of all people,

08:50.963 --> 08:53.466
missing the point of a joke.

08:53.466 --> 08:54.467
(laughing)

08:54.467 --> 08:56.469
Hey, don't worry about
it, Miss Chambers.

08:56.469 --> 08:57.970
It even happens to me.

09:03.392 --> 09:05.278
NORM: Sammy, uh, what
time you got there, man?

09:05.278 --> 09:07.230
11:15.

09:07.230 --> 09:10.233
11:15. How did it get so late so early?

09:10.233 --> 09:12.735
I'd better be getting home to, uh, Vera.

09:12.735 --> 09:14.237
(yawning): Oh, yeah.

09:14.237 --> 09:17.623
(everybody talking and yawning)

09:20.576 --> 09:22.578
Yeah, you know what they say:

09:22.578 --> 09:25.081
"An early bird catches
the obsessive-compulsive."

09:25.581 --> 09:26.582
(laughing)

09:27.083 --> 09:28.968
'Night, Sam.

09:28.968 --> 09:31.887
MAN: Oh, boy!

09:31.887 --> 09:34.890
They sure took off in
a hurry, didn't they?

09:34.890 --> 09:38.761
Yeah, but that doesn't seem
suspicious to you, does it?

09:41.147 --> 09:44.517
No, I... I guess not.

09:44.517 --> 09:46.068
Oh, hey, I have an idea.

09:46.068 --> 09:47.270
You go in the back

09:47.270 --> 09:49.989
and total these receipts,
and we'll get out of here.

09:49.989 --> 09:51.907
Okay.

09:51.907 --> 09:53.409
All right.

09:53.409 --> 09:55.411
Say, Woody, when I come back out here,

09:55.411 --> 09:58.414
there's not going to be a
surprise for me, is there?

09:58.414 --> 09:59.915
A surprise party, maybe?

09:59.915 --> 10:00.916
No.

10:00.916 --> 10:03.169
You're not lying, are you?

10:03.169 --> 10:05.955
Sam, you'd know if I was lying.

10:05.955 --> 10:07.840
I'd... I'd tell you.

10:10.126 --> 10:12.128
Right. I'll, uh, I'll be in my office.

10:12.128 --> 10:13.379
WOODY: All right.

10:17.683 --> 10:18.684
Come on in, guys.

10:18.684 --> 10:20.186
He doesn't suspect a thing.

10:22.688 --> 10:24.190
Come on down, fellas.

10:25.691 --> 10:27.693
(half-whispers)

10:29.695 --> 10:31.197
Shh, shh, shh, shh.

10:36.786 --> 10:40.539
Okay? In the words of the
immortal bard, "Party!"

10:40.539 --> 10:42.041
(silent cheering)

10:44.126 --> 10:47.129
Uh, Sam, you can go home now.

10:48.130 --> 10:49.999
EVERYONE: Surprise!

10:49.999 --> 10:52.251
(whooping and cheering)

10:52.251 --> 10:54.754
(laughter and applause)

10:54.754 --> 10:57.640
Wow!

10:57.640 --> 11:01.927
Sam, you should have seen
the look on your face!

11:08.067 --> 11:10.519
(music playing on video)

11:13.522 --> 11:14.523
SAM: Ooh!

11:14.523 --> 11:16.025
FRASIER: Hey!

11:16.025 --> 11:17.026
All right!

11:17.026 --> 11:18.027
(guys whooping)

11:18.027 --> 11:19.528
Boy! Thanks, guys.

11:19.528 --> 11:20.529
Yeah, man.

11:20.529 --> 11:23.032
That last scene gave me new
respect for rowing machines.

11:23.032 --> 11:24.917
I hear you, bud. Ooh!

11:24.917 --> 11:28.871
Hey, you guys, oh! Thank you.

11:28.871 --> 11:29.872
This has been fantastic.

11:30.373 --> 11:31.257
I have to admit

11:31.257 --> 11:32.508
that I used to think
that bachelor parties

11:33.008 --> 11:33.876
were kind of embarrassing.

11:33.876 --> 11:34.627
Get the lights!

11:34.627 --> 11:36.512
SAM: Oh, God, not again...

11:36.512 --> 11:38.464
(guys cheering)

11:45.771 --> 11:46.772
Girl in there, right?

11:46.772 --> 11:48.274
Well...

11:48.274 --> 11:50.142
Just your type.

11:52.945 --> 11:55.231
So make the obligatory
speech and have at her!

11:55.231 --> 11:56.649
GUYS: Yeah!

11:56.649 --> 11:59.402
Oh, no, I can't do it.

11:59.402 --> 12:00.903
I... you know... (scoffs)

12:00.903 --> 12:02.405
No, I-I know you went
to a lot of trouble.

12:02.405 --> 12:05.291
I'm sorry, but it
just wouldn't be right.

12:05.291 --> 12:07.209
CLIFF: What? Come on,
Sammy. What is this?

12:07.209 --> 12:10.079
Malone, King of the Road!

12:10.079 --> 12:13.833
(everyone whooping)

12:13.833 --> 12:15.217
Better make hay, buddy.

12:15.217 --> 12:16.218
After this, it is one woman

12:16.218 --> 12:17.720
for the rest of your life. Oh, boy.

12:17.720 --> 12:20.089
EVERYONE: Yeah...

12:21.590 --> 12:26.595
I-I never really thought
about it in those terms before.

12:26.595 --> 12:29.482
One woman for the rest of my life.

12:29.482 --> 12:31.233
(everyone chuckles) I
mean, don't get me wrong.

12:31.233 --> 12:33.602
I mean, she's... she's a...
she's a great woman, but, uh...

12:33.602 --> 12:35.821
there's only one of her...

12:37.656 --> 12:39.825
...for the rest of my life.

12:39.825 --> 12:41.277
But, you know, it'll go quickly.

12:41.277 --> 12:43.162
Just go-go ahead, cut the cake.

12:44.113 --> 12:45.614
Boy, it really makes you think.

12:45.614 --> 12:48.117
You know, I've been a
bachelor a good long time.

12:48.117 --> 12:51.003
I mean, a good lot of women.

12:51.003 --> 12:53.873
Now there won't be any more women.

12:53.873 --> 12:55.758
Just woman.

12:55.758 --> 12:57.376
One woman.

12:57.376 --> 12:59.345
Yeah, but what a woman!

12:59.345 --> 13:01.263
I mean, you know what? I've got an idea.

13:01.263 --> 13:02.264
Why don't we have some cake?

13:02.264 --> 13:05.017
(everyone agreeing)

13:05.017 --> 13:06.802
One perfume.

13:07.303 --> 13:08.804
One set of earlobes.

13:08.804 --> 13:11.190
Not, not even sensitive earlobes.

13:12.558 --> 13:17.813
One pair of lips flapping in my ears...

13:17.813 --> 13:19.732
day after day until I die.

13:19.732 --> 13:21.734
Oh, my God!

13:21.734 --> 13:23.202
Sammy, Sammy, that's great.

13:23.202 --> 13:25.704
Look, we got a big,
wonderful cake here, you know,

13:25.704 --> 13:28.207
with a... with a very
special surprise inside...

13:28.207 --> 13:32.161
which just might spoil
if you don't shut up!

13:33.162 --> 13:36.165
Uh... I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

13:36.165 --> 13:37.166
What am I doing?

13:37.166 --> 13:38.918
I mean, if I'm going to tie myself

13:38.918 --> 13:40.753
to the old ball and
chain, I might as well get

13:40.753 --> 13:43.255
one last night of freedom in here.

13:43.255 --> 13:45.257
(everyone agreeing)
Okay, bring her out here.

13:45.257 --> 13:46.141
Strap her on.

13:46.141 --> 13:47.059
Come on.

13:47.059 --> 13:48.060
EVERYONE: Yeah!

13:51.564 --> 13:54.066
Strap this on!

14:05.911 --> 14:09.415
Sam, you should see
the look on your face!

14:15.204 --> 14:16.071
Hi, guys.

14:16.572 --> 14:17.957
Hey, Carla, how was traffic school?

14:17.957 --> 14:19.291
Eh, it was all right.

14:19.792 --> 14:20.292
